  <!-- @import "site-sidebar.kit" -->

  <p>
    All modals in Codebase slide in from the top and appear flush with the top of the window (but you can move them in by adding a margin (or <code>.deco-margin-top</code>) to the modal body). The reset-overlay is raised and darkened, Modals can be dismissed by clicking their <code>.modal__close</code> button (or icon) or by clicking the reset-overlay.
  </p>

  <p>
    The simplest modal is <code>.modal--narrow</code> with no modal header or footer:
  </p>

  <div id="modal-1" class="modal modal--narrow deco-bs">
    <div class="modal__body deco-p-lg deco-bg-white">
      Modal body content.
      <hr />
      <a class="modal__close float--right">Close</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    <button class="btn modal__open" data-modal="modal-1">Show modal (1): simple</button>
  </p>

  <p>
    Modal with header and footer and more decoration:
  </p>

  <div id="modal-2" class="modal modal--narrow deco-mt-lg deco-b-thick-solid deco-b-warning deco-b-radius deco-bs deco-bg-white">
    <div class="modal__header deco-bb-thin-solid deco-p-sm">
      <span class="modal__close float--right"><i class="fa fa-times fa-border"></i></span>
      <h4>Modal header</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="modal__body deco-p-block">
      Modal body content
    </div>
    <div class="modal__footer deco-bt-thin-solid deco-p-sm clearfix">
      Modal footer
      <button class="btn btn--secondary modal__close float--right">Close</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    <button class="btn modal__open" data-modal="modal-2">Show modal (2): with header and footer</button>
  </p>

  <pre><code class="language-none">&lt;div id="modal-2" class="modal modal--narrow"&gt;

  &lt;div class="modal__header"&gt;
    &lt;span class="modal__close float--right"&gt;&lt;i class="fa fa-times fa-border"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;h4&gt;Modal header&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="modal__body deco-p-block"&gt;
    Modal body content
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="modal__footer clearfix"&gt;
    Modal footer
    &lt;button class="btn btn--secondary modal__close float--right"&gt;Close&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;button class="btn modal__open" data-modal="modal-2"&gt;Show modal 2&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>
    Remove the modifier class <code>.modal--narrow</code> and instead add <code>.modal--contains-grid</code> if you require your modal to expand to contain a grid system:
